parse.description: A collection of parsing instructions can be used to define the data types of string-valued attributes in the JSON file. Each instruction is a name-value pair, where the name is the name of the attribute, and the value is the desired data type (one of `"number"`, `"boolean"` or `"date"`). For example, `"parse": {"modified_on": "date"}` parses the `modified_on` field in each input record a Date value. Specific date formats can be provided (e.g., `{foo: 'date:"%m%d%Y"'}`), using the [d3-time-format syntax](https://github.com/d3/d3-time-format#locale_format). UTC date format parsing is supported similarly (e.g., `{foo: 'utc:"%m%d%Y"'}`). See more about [UTC time](timeunit.html#utc)

filter.description: A string containing the filter Vega expression. Use `datum` to refer to the current data object.
